article.description: Redshirt freshman Stephanie Holzer scored 19 of her 26 points in the second half of her first start, helping Vanderbilt (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP) pull away for a 70-60 victory over a pesky Samford team Thursday night.
article.headline: Stephanie Holzer scores 19 of 26 points in second half for Vanderbilt
article.linkText: Holzer's 2nd-half burst powers Vanderbilt to win
article.story:
NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Redshirt freshman Stephanie Holzer scored 19 of her 26 points in the second half of her first start, helping Vanderbilt (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP) pull away for a 70-60 victory over a pesky Samford team Thursday night.

Holzer, injured last season, had nine rebounds and two blocks. The 6-foot-4 center scored 11 straight points in the second half for Vanderbilt (2-0).

Savannah Hill hit three 3-pointers and scored 20 points for Samford (0-2), which made nine 3-pointers. Shelby Campbell chipped in 10 points.

Commodores senior Hannah Tuomi had a double-double with 14 points and 10 rebounds, and freshman Jasmine Lister scored 14 points with a trio of 3-pointers. Vanderbilt, with two starting guards out with injuries, plays at No. 14 Florida State on Sunday.

The Bulldogs fought back from a 12-point deficit to tie it 28-all on back-to-back 3s by Hill and Hannah Dawson 2 1/2 minutes after halftime.
